ce:section.ce:para:
To obtain accurate proofs, flow cytometry was used to determine the transfection efficiencies of PEI/DNA with mass ratio of 1:1 and CC NCs/DNA condensates with different mass ratios of 5:1, 10:1, and 20:1 at pH 7.4 and 6.5, respectively (Fig. 11
                        ). The transfection efficiencies of CC NCs/DNA condensates with different mass ratios at pH 6.5 were about 11.9%, 12.3%, and 14.2% respectively, which were much higher than those (2.08%, 2.78%, and 3.07%) at pH 7.4. The reason may be that the charge targeting ability at low pH of CC NCs enhanced the endocytosis of HepG2 cells, inducing more transfection of pEGFP condensates in cells. It is also seen that transfection of all CC NCs/DNA condensates with different mass ratios were lower than that (16.0%) of PEI/DNA condensates at the mass ratio of 1:1. However, the obvious cytotoxicity of PEI could cause cells death as high as 90% at the concentration of 40 μg·mL−1 
                        [37], which was much higher than that of the obtained CC NCs at the same concentration (Fig. 6a). Thus, the above results demonstrated that the synthesized CC NCs were multifunctional gene carriers with good transfection ability and biocompatibility, possessing huge potential in the application of synergistic photothermal, photodynamic, and gene therapies for cancer treatment.
